# Optional waiting list

The member waiting list is now an optional feature. Existing organizations keep it enabled so the current validation flow stays unchanged, but it can be disabled from the [Waiting list settings](/settings#waiting_list) if you don't need a capacity-based waiting list.

When the feature is disabled, validating a complete registration creates the membership directly and activates the member. Registrations still arrive in the list of members to validate first, so admins keep the same review step.

One email detail to keep in mind: registrations validated without immediate activation, such as support members or members placed on the waiting list, use the "Member validated" template. Direct activation uses the ["Member activated" template](/mail_templates/member_activated). If you disable the waiting list, make sure that template says what you want new active members to receive.

You can read more about member statuses in [the members handbook](/handbook/members#statuses).
